stylometry: Some of the things the output from @RISK shows you is the mean, median, minimum value, maximum value, and standard deviation. When looking to make a decision about things, like how many calendars to order, you should weigh all of the information. Just because one of the simulations displays a high average does not mean it is the best solution. This answer may also have the highest standard deviation, which would then mean the answer is probably not the best simulation. You should look at all of the information before making a decision. A not so high average with a low standard deviation may end up being the best possible decision.
